name: BayPackets
overview: As of August 30, 2006, BayPackets, Inc. was acquired by GenBand, Inc. BayPackets, Inc., a communications software company, provides IP multimedia subsystem compliant multi-network voice and data solutions for wireless, wireline, and cable operators. The company offers network services platform that interoperate with network elements, such as media servers and soft switches; pre-paid application, an IP-based solution, which allows service providers to deploy prepaid service on wireline and wireless networks; and personal communication manager that enables the service providers to deliver call routing and call management functions. It also provides Voice VPN that allows enterprises to implement their private voice network that interconnects multiple office locations; mobility management application server, which allows the operators to provide roaming capability to their subscribers; and SIP application server, a platform for delivering applications for the telecommunication networks. In addition, the company offers videomail service that provides a message box with text, voice, and video for VOIP, and wireless consumers; unified communications application that offers a set of features, including multi-network, feature packaging, and service billing; and multimedia ringback tones that integrate with content providers to enable video ring-back tones for voice over Internet protocol and wireless consumers. It serves consumer/SOHO, small/medium business, and enterprise market segments. The company was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Fremont, California.
